<h1>{{ title }}</h1>
<p>What began as a simple way of keeping track of what my small book club was reading has evolved into a way of mainlining static site web development into the veins of my existence. </p>
<p>I wanted simplicity. Security. File as app. I found 11ty (eleventy) and starteed playing around. At first, I thought it was pretty great, but I had to go through testing others before I made a decision. I tried Hugo, Jekyll, and Gatsby, but they all had their own quirks and complexities that I didn't want to deal with. 11ty was the clear winner for me. It's simple, flexible, and has a great community behind it. Plus, it's built on JavaScript, which is my language of choice, coming mainly from a front end designer perspective.  </p>
<p>Anyway, I hope you enjoy the site. Maybe you'll find some book recommendations. My list of favorites is below. </p>
<p>If you have any questions, comments, or suggestions, please don't hesitate to reach out to me at davidrosshk@gmail.com. Spammers, very frowned upon in my jurisdiction, will be sent a fourteen page subpoena from the courts by droneServe, a local startup with better precision than Swiss watches. </p>
<p>So it's not much of a blog yet, and it's gone through a few iterations, some of which featured travel photography, but I think I want to focus on reading and some personal writing that I won't be featuring pulicly. </p>